OL,5, The number of pupils regularly missing 
OL,6, school in England has not returned to  
OL,7, pre-Covid pandemic levels, according to
OL,8, official statistics.                   
OL,10,FA quarter (25.1%) of pupils were       
OL,11,Fpersistently absent last term, compared
OL,12,Fwith 13.1% in the autumn term of 2019. 
OL,14,FThe government said the absence rate   
OL,15,Fwas driven by illness, with high levels
OL,16,Fof flu and other viruses circulating.  
OL,18,FIt said it was "offering targeted help"
OL,19,Ffor children who were regularly off    
OL,20,Fschool.                                
